Food was nasty, lacked flavor, chicken was undercooked even though it looked cooked on the outside but wasn't fully cooked on the inside. The pictures of the food looked really good on google maps which is what lured me here in the first place but it didn't live up to it's images. I was completly surprised by it since it looked so good at first both in pictures and in person but it all made sense when I saw someone inside the restaurant prepping the food real nice on a platter and photographing it while using a ring light to enhance the quality of the pictures. No wonder it looked so good. If only they spent as much time as they did cooking the food right instead of photographing it then maybe the expensive platters would have been worth every dime. Don't get me wrong, the platters looked good and their menu has alot of potential but the quality of the food and taste just wasn't there. I was going to give it one star but I'll give it two just because the waitress was nice and the service she provided was good. They should work on making the food taste as good as it looks and then it'll be worth 5 stars. Maybe one day I'll give it a second chance and we'll see if they lived up to their google images next time around.

Amazing place and the owner is really friendly. He’ll help you decide what to order and give a couple of suggestions. Everything on the menu is good. The food is very good, I had a chicken arepa, the chicken has flavor to it and wasn’t dry, the inside was fill with veggies that had a nice hint of lime that complimented the whole arepa as a whole. I also had a salchipapa, the fries were well made, and had a crunch to them from the outside. The hot dog to fries ratio was very good. It wasn’t like most place where the ratio is off and give you so many fries and barely any hot dog. The food come out very quick after order. If you want a quick snack try their charred cob, it had a good charred ratio that doesn’t just feel like you eating burn corn, you still taste charred but it not over powering, the corn keeps it sweetness even after being charred. I also tried their sangria slushy, it was super good, had a kick to it but was super refreshing. The establishment had games on the side so it’s prefect for a hang out with a few friends. The environment is welcoming and very clean. The waitress is very nice and attentive, bring the food to you when it’s out. This place a must and I would be coming back again anytime I’m in the area. Side note This place has tv that place whatever game is on. So you can come out and eat without missing any of the highlights.
